Storytime: Naush is a much better cook than me. His parents are absolutely amazing in the kitchen, and Naush grew up learning from them. My parents are amazing cooks too, but they didn’t pressure me to learn. When Naush & I first got married, he did most of the cooking, but now, I actually enjoy it. I don’t think I’ll ever be as good as him, but I’m determined to learn. Grateful for a partner that never put me down in the kitchen & was always encouraging when I tried.

I had a trip booked this week to Cancun, and I was unsure if I should go with everything going on in the world… 

But then, my baby’s movements began to slow down & I felt her move extremely low.

They say a baby in the womb feels all of their mother’s emotions, and I’d been crying nonstop for two weeks. 

So I decided to go, and by day 2 on the trip, I could feel baby’s movements pick up again. 

I am grateful I was able to take a short break for her sake, but I’m also acutely aware of what a privilege it is to be able to travel… 

So while out of town, I continued to work on a charity event that I’ll be co-hosting with several incredible women in Houston. 

It’s this Sunday. Please see my IG stories for details.

I still can’t believe we pulled this off…

1 week ago, a group of girls sat down to dinner & decided to create a fundraising event for the children that have been orphaned in Gaza…

And within that week, we acquired 40+ vendors, $60k+ in donations, and a fully packed event from start to finish.
